This pseudopotential is part of the Schlipf-Gygi norm-conserving pseudopotential library. Its construction parameters were tuned to reproduce materials of a training set with very high accuracy and should be suitable as a general purpose pseudopotential to treat a variety of different compounds. For details of the construction and testing of the pseudopotential please refer to:
M. Schlipf, F. Gygi, Comp. Phys. Comm. 196, 36 (2015) http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.cpc.2015.05.011
We kindly ask that you include this reference in all publications associated to this pseudopotential.
